==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: electronics
<hw>electronics</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the branch of
physics that deals with the behavior of electrons. Electronics is
primarily concerned with phenomena other than simple conduction, such as
emission of electrons, storage of electrical charge, the effects of
electrical fields on the conduction of electrons through a circuit, and
amplification and manipulation of electric signals such as voltage or
current by design of circuits. Electronics also encompasses the
application of such fundamental principles to the construction of
devices using the manipulation of electrons in their operation, known as
<er>electronic devices</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the branch of engineering concerned with design of
devices using the principles of electronics, for practical
purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>electronic devices generally, or the electronic
circuits within an electronic device.</def> <illu>The Russian harvesters
are sturdily constructed, but their <ex>electronics</ex> are
primitive.</illu>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>electron-volt</ent>⟦br⟧
